headline: Cisco and Brinker earnings, Fed commentary: What to Watch
summary: Yahoo Finance Senior Reporter Allie Canal takes a look at the top stories for investors to watch on Wednesday, Aug. 13. In the morning, Brinker (EAT) will report its fourth quarter earnings. Cisco (CSCO) will release fourth quarter results in the afternoon, with its 2025 forecast in focus among investors. Richmond Fed President Tom Barkin will be speaking in the morning, while Chicago Fed President Austan Goolsbee and Atlanta Fed President Raphael Bostic will deliver remarks in the afternoon. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.
